<subSubSection id="E7A2B298FFD0786F6FBE18B3FD537AAE" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFD0786F6FBE18B3FD537AAE" blockId="37.[151,1436,258,1038]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFD0786F6FBE18B3FE877ACB" bold="true" box="[199,334,907,931]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is a patronym named after Dr. Murray Fletcher for his outstanding work on leafhoppers of the Australian biogeographical region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E7A2B298FFD0786F6FBE18EBFB937D66" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFD0786F6FBE18EBFB937D66" blockId="37.[151,1436,258,1038]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFD0786F6FBE18EBFEF27A83" bold="true" box="[199,315,979,1003]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is nearest to 
<taxonomicName id="68B89A90FFD0786F6D1518EBFD187A83" authority="Nielson, 2011" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" box="[620,721,979,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evansolidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFD0786F6D1518EBFDB47A82" box="[620,637,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">E</emphasis>
. lyrata
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFD0786F6DAB18EBFD1F7A83" box="[722,726,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">,</emphasis>
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFD0786F6DA718EBFCF07A83" bold="true" box="[734,825,979,1003]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="86FF807AFFD0786F6DA718EBFCF07A83" box="[734,825,979,1003]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and can be distinguished by greater number of spines (6) on the aedeagal shaft and configuration of the style which is narrower in basal 1/3.
</paragraph>
